The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Oct. 26 (PTI): A plea by Major Sumit Sharma, posted in Jammu, for quitting the army to take care of his ailing father has been rejected. The armed forces tribunal has held that he was an unmanned aerial vehicle specialist whose services could not be dispensed with in national interest.          
	Sharma had urged the tribunal to direct the army to accept his resignation with immediate effect after his unit refused him a posting in Delhi.                  
	 Chennai (PTI): The names of LTTE chief V. Prabhakaran and his deputy Pottu Amman have been removed from the list of accused in the Rajiv Gandhi assassination case by a court in Chennai as both are now dead.                  
	 Hyderabad (PTI): An 11-month-old was stolen from a government hospital in Hyderabad allegedly by a burqa-clad woman, police said on Tuesday. The parents of the boy lodged a complaint with the police after the child went missing on Monday night from the hospital.                  
	 Lucknow (PTI): An FIR was registered on Tuesday against the BSP MLA from Isauli, Chandrabhadra Singh, and nine others in Faizabad for allegedly abducting and killing the husband of a panchayat poll candidate, police said.                   
	 Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): A ban on display of religious motifs on state-operated special bus services to pilgrim centres has sparked protests from organisations alleging that this move was targeted against the Sabarimala pilgrimage that begins next month. The directive says words like Swami Saranam and Amme Narayana should not be displayed on the buses.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): A clerk of Syndicate Bank was sentenced to five years rigorous imprisonment with a fine of Rs 22,000 for causing a loss of over Rs 37 lakh to the bank. Praveen Kumar Gupta has manipulated and tampered with the stock invest accounts, ledger and stock invest instruments.
                                                                                                                                              
